{#- sing-box AnyTLS server config, rendered by `tasks/config.yml`.

  One AnyTLS inbound on an internal loopback port. HAProxy passes the
  AnyTLS domain's TLS straight through (mode tcp, SNI match), so sing-box
  terminates TLS itself. Authentication reuses `naive_proxy_users`; the
  password doubles as the AnyTLS shared secret. Secrets come from role
  variables — never hardcode them here.

  TLS / certificate:
    * ACME (production, `_naive_proxy_anytls_acme`): sing-box obtains and
      renews its own Let's Encrypt certificate via built-in CertMagic.
      `disable_http_challenge` is set because only :443 is routed to the
      pod (no :80), so issuance uses TLS-ALPN-01. `alternative_tls_port`
      is the internal listener port: sing-box runs ManageSync BEFORE the
      AnyTLS listener binds, so during the FIRST issuance CertMagic must
      bind this port itself to answer the challenge (HAProxy forwards the
      acme-tls/1 + SNI handshake here). On renewals the listener already
      holds the port, CertMagic's bind attempt backs off, and the
      challenge is answered inline on the same listener. Leaving this at
      the default (443) would make CertMagic collide with HAProxy and the
      challenge would never be answered.
    * Static (`molecule_mode` / ACME disabled): a certificate prepared at
      `/anytls-certs/{fullchain,key}.pem` is used directly, so tests never
      depend on public Let's Encrypt issuance.
-#}
{%- set _users = [] -%}
{%- for _name, _pass in naive_proxy_users.items() -%}
  {%- set _ = _users.append({'name': _name, 'password': _pass}) -%}
{%- endfor -%}
{%- if _naive_proxy_anytls_acme | bool -%}
  {%- set _acme_provider = (naive_proxy_molecule_mode | bool)
        | ternary(_naive_proxy_pebble_acme_server, naive_proxy_anytls_acme_provider) -%}
  {%- set _tls = {
    'enabled': true,
    'server_name': naive_proxy_anytls_domain,
    'acme': {
      'domain': [naive_proxy_anytls_domain],
      'data_directory': '/acme-data',
      'email': naive_proxy_anytls_acme_email,
      'provider': _acme_provider,
      'disable_http_challenge': true,
      'alternative_tls_port': _naive_proxy_anytls_port | int
    }
  } -%}
{%- else -%}
  {%- set _tls = {
    'enabled': true,
    'server_name': naive_proxy_anytls_domain,
    'certificate_path': '/anytls-certs/fullchain.pem',
    'key_path': '/anytls-certs/key.pem'
  } -%}
{%- endif -%}
{#- ALPN must be advertised so uTLS/browser clients (which send h2,http/1.1)
    can negotiate; on the ACME path sing-box prepends it ahead of acme-tls/1.
    `_naive_proxy_anytls_alpn` is empty unless uTLS is enabled (see vars/main.yml). -#}
{%- if _naive_proxy_anytls_alpn -%}
  {%- set _tls = _tls | combine({'alpn': _naive_proxy_anytls_alpn}) -%}
{%- endif -%}
{{ {
  'log': {'level': naive_proxy_anytls_log_level, 'timestamp': true},
  'inbounds': [
    {
      'type': 'anytls',
      'tag': 'anytls-in',
      'listen': '127.0.0.1',
      'listen_port': _naive_proxy_anytls_port | int,
      'users': _users,
      'tls': _tls
    }
  ],
  'outbounds': [
    {'type': 'direct', 'tag': 'direct'}
  ]
} | to_nice_json }}
